The paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on semantic relation classification between entity pairs in sentences. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a novel end-to-end recurrent neural model, which incorporates an entity-aware attention mechanism with a latent entity typing method, indicating that it may fall under the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses experimental results to demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed model, suggesting that it may also belong to the categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
